FBIS3-34465 "drnes027_g_94005" FBIS-NES-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 Sudan Opposition Blames Government for Aiding `Terrorists' NC0802162294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1515 GMT 8 Feb 93 NC0802162294 Cairo MENA Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Cairo, 8 Feb (MENA)--The Sudanese opposition al-Ummah Party issued a statement in Cairo today holding the Sudanese Government fully responsible for opening the country's territory to terrorists and noting, in this connection, the Sudanese Foreign Ministry's decision to grant citizenship to members of all Islamic groups. The party announced that the Sudanese Government is responsible for last Saturday's assault against the residence and company headquarters of a Saudi businessman living in Sudan. Several security personnel were injured in that incident. The statement warned the Sudanese Government of the consequences of playing patron to terrorists.
